`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
Three patterns confirmed: (1) `Bucket.first` is the correct typed API for first-entity access — `query[0]` compiles in JS but TypeScript rejects it since `Bucket` doesn't declare numeric index signatures. (2) When bridging ECS to React Native (non-R3F) components, `useEntities(query)` from `miniplex-react` is the only hook needed — it subscribes to add/remove events and triggers re-renders, then you read the data synchronously from the query in the same render. (3) The RAIN_DISPLAY_RATIO pattern (3D budget × small factor = 2D display count) is a clean way to tie 2D overlay counts to config values without hardcoding separate constants.
